        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 3:13AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 313 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 7 miles northwest of Stanton, or 11 miles north of
Greenwood, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sand Springs, Tarzan, Sparenberg, Lomax, Vincent, Coahoma, Stanton,
Lenorah, Big Spring, Big Spring Country Club, Courtney, Big Spring
McMahon-Wrinkle Airpark, Knott, Vealmoor, Ackerly, Gail, Stanton
Municipal Aiport, Luther, Elbow, and J B Thomas Reservoir.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 151 and 196.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
